g%3Efederal%20education%20bill%2C%20made%20public%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20also%20proposes%20that%20after%20finding%20a%20healthcare%20job%2C%20medical%20graduates%20from%20state-funded%20schools%20must%20continue%20working%20for%20three%20years.%20Their%20other%20option%20is%20to%20continue%20their%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-companies-say-they-have-duty-send-medicine-to-russia-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia's%20medical%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20funded%20by%20or%20affiliated%20with%20the%20government%2C%20with%20lawmakers%20saying%20154%20institutions%20and%20scientific%20organizations%20draw%20from%20federal%2C%20state%2C%20and%20local%20budgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20business%20daily%20Kommersant%20estimated%20in%20February%20that%20it%20costs%20the%20state%20about%20%242%2C480%20a%20year%20to%20train%20a%20medical%20student.%20As%20such%2C%20under%20the%20new%20bill%2C%20if%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-medical-workers-16-times-more-likely-die-from-coronavirus-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20medical%20student%3C%2Fa%3E%20undergoes%20the%20typical%20six%20years%20of%20training%2C%20they%20could%20face%20a%20fine%20of%20%2442%2C000%20or%20higher%20if%20they%20don't%20find%20a%20job%20within%20a%20year%20of%20graduation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalculations%20for%20the%20fines%20would%20be%20up%20to%20the%20Russian%20government%2C%20the%20bill%20added.%20If%20these%20measures%20become%20law%2C%20they%20would%20take%20effect%20on%20January%201%2C%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESergei%20Leonov%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Russian%20State%20Duma's%20healthcare%20committee%2C%20told%20local%20media%20on%20Monday%20that%20parliament%20was%20ready%20to%20support%20the%20bill%2C%20but%20could%20tighten%20it%20with%20further%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20they%20violate%20their%20obligations%20to%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20graduates%20avoiding%20hospital%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22859959c7-bb6f-4cbc-8439-96f2d272109a%5C%22%3EA%20bleak%20outlook%20for%20Russia's%20medical%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20country%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20underscores%20a%20shortage%20of%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20in%20Russia%2C%20which%20authorities%20fear%20will%20escalate%20into%20a%20national%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Russia's%20health%20minister%2C%20Mikhail%20Murashko%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Finterfax.ru%2Frussia%2F1010663%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20local%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20country%20was%20short%20of%20about%2023%2C300%20doctors%20and%2063%2C500%20%26quot%3Bmidlevel%26quot%3B%20personnel%2C%20which%20includes%20nurses%20and%20technicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20about%20550%2C000%20doctors%20already%20in%20Russia's%20workforce%2C%20per%20Murashko.%20But%20he%20added%20that%20nearly%20a%20fifth%20of%20these%20professionals%20are%20over%2060%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20country%20is%20struggling%20to%20recruit%20young%20doctors%20and%20nurses%2C%20even%20after%20they%20finish%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20note%20attached%20to%20the%20new%20bill%2C%20the%20health%20ministry%20said%20that%20in%20state-affiliated%20schools%2C%2035%25%20of%20graduates%20from%20higher%20medical%20education%20and%2040%25%20of%20graduates%20in%20vocational%20medical%20education%20don't%20work%20in%20state%20or%20public%20health%20organizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow%20and%20inconsistent%20pay%20is%20often%20blamed%20for%20young%20medical%20graduates%20shirking%20hospital%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20lawmaker%20Galina%20Izotova%2C%20who%20serves%20in%20the%20government%20chamber%20that%20audits%20federal%20budgets%2C%20said%20in%20March%20that%20doctors'%20salaries%20in%2021%20of%20Russia's%2089%20regions%20hadn't%20reached%20the%20minimum%20level%20mandated%20by%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20remains%20significant%20variation%20in%20salary%20levels%20between%20neighboring%20regions%2C%20contributing%20to%20labor%20migration.%20In%20some%20regions%2C%20salary%20differences%20can%20be%20three%20times%20or%20greater%2C%26quot%3B%20Izotova%20told%20the%20Duma%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Doctors%20of%20the%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20a%20professional%20community%20for%20medical%20workers%2C%20surveyed%202%2C030%20doctors%20in%20March%202024%2C%2078.9%25%20of%20them%20said%20they%20had%20to%20work%20more%20than%20one%20job%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20two-thirds%20of%20them%2C%20including%20doctors%20in%20the%20Moscow%20region%2C%20said%20that%20they%20were%20drawing%20monthly%20salaries%20of%20%24727%20or%20less.%20That%20could%20indicate%20a%20wide%20imbalance%20in%20wages%20across%20the%20country%2C%20since%20Russia's%20federal%20statistics%20service%20reported%20that%20the%20average%20physician's%20salary%20was%20about%20%241%2C400%20from%20January%20to%20June%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20also%20struggling%20with%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-outlook-ukraine-war-worker-shortage-population-brain-drain-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20drain%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20highly%20educated%20and%20skilled%20workers%20since%20it%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%202022%2C%20with%20a%20million%20citizens%2C%20mostly%20young%20and%20college-educated%20people%2C%20leaving%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effects%20of%20the%20departures%2C%20compounded%20with%20the%20war's%20toll%20on%20Russian%20lives%2C%20led%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-lacks-workers-ukraine-war-labor-crisis-worker-shortage-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20shortage%20of%20some%205%20million%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20